!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

smooth /smuːð/

(smoothing,smoothed,smoother,smooths,smoothest) 

1. ADJ A smooth surface has no roughness, lumps, or holes. 光滑的 

例： ...a rich cream that keeps skin soft and smooth. …一种可以保持皮肤柔软光滑的富含营养的护肤霜。 

例： ...a smooth surface such as glass. …玻璃般光滑的表面。 

2. ADJ A smooth liquid or mixture has been mixed well so that it has no lumps. 均匀的; (液体或混合物) 细腻的 

例： Continue whisking until the mixture looks smooth and creamy. 继续搅拌直至混合物看上去均匀且呈奶油状。 

3. ADJ If you describe a drink such as wine, whisky, or coffee as smooth , you mean that it is not bitter and is pleasant to drink. (酒或咖啡等饮料) 醇和的 

例： This makes the whiskies much smoother. 这使威士忌酒醇和得多。 

4. ADJ A smooth line or movement has no sudden breaks or changes in direction or speed. (线条或动作) 流畅的 

例： This exercise is done in one smooth motion. 这套体操是由一个流畅的动作完成的。 

5. smoothly ADV 流畅地 [ADV with v] 

例： Make sure that you execute all movements smoothly and without jerking. 确保你流畅、无颤动地完成所有动作。 

6. ADJ A smooth ride, flight, or sea crossing is very comfortable because there are no unpleasant movements. (乘车﹑飞行或航海) 舒适平稳的 

例： The active suspension system gives the car a very smooth ride. 活动的悬挂系统使汽车行驶起来非常平稳。 

7. ADJ You use smooth to describe something that is going well and is free of problems or trouble. 顺利的 

例： Political hopes for a swift and smooth transition to democracy have been dashed. 向民主快速顺利的过渡的政治愿望已经破灭了。 

8. smoothly ADV 顺利地 [ADV with v] 

例： So far, talks at GM have gone smoothly. 迄今，在通用汽车公司的会谈进展顺利。 

9. ADJ If you describe a man as smooth , you mean that he is extremely smart, confident, and polite, often in a way that you find rather unpleasant. 精明的; 圆滑的 

例： Twelve extremely good-looking, smooth young men have been picked as finalists. 12个非常英俊精明的男青年已被选为参加决赛的选手。 

10. V-T If you smooth something, you move your hands over its surface to make it smooth and flat. (用手) 弄平 

例： She stood up and smoothed down her frock. 她站了起来，抚平了自己的连衣裙。

